// Returns a textual version of a number with up to twenty digits that will sort
//   correctly in alphabetical sorting. For example, sorting "10" and "2" in
//   normal alphabetical order would sort the "10" first. This converts both to
//   a format such that the "2" will appear first when sorting in ascending
//   order.
//
// EXTNERAL REQUIREMENTS: The PadZeros custom function.
//
// Written by Charles Ross

Right( padd.PadZeros( _number; 20 ); 20 )
